<DOC><DOCNO> AP881121-0144 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-21-88 1759EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-MotelCrime     11-21 0196</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Motel Crime,0200</SECOND><HEAD>Blood-Stained Mattress Leads to Murder Probe</HEAD><DATELINE>EAST LYME, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The discovery of a bloodstained mattressin a motel has led police in Connecticut and Georgia to begin amurder investigation, although authorities said Monday no body hasbeen recovered.   A maid entered Room 12 at the Starlight Motel in East Lyme nearthe Connecticut shoreline about noon last Friday to find that amattress that ``had been stained with a large quantity of blood,''state police said in a statement.   Two men riding in a gray or silver Cadillac with a Georgiaregistration had checked into the motel room on Nov. 15 for severaldays, and left before the discovery, state police said.   Police said they are working on the case with the Georgia Bureauof Investigation, issuing a nationwide alert in an effort to findthe men.   State police said they are not aware of any missing person'sreport that might have been linked to the incident.   Marcy Stamm, a state police spokeswoman, said no weapon was foundin the room. She said police would not comment on other evidencethat led them to conclude a crime had occurred.</TEXT></DOC>